      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CLASSIC ROYALE (7) will be fitter for the fresh run at this track and trip where he never really fired a shot. Back to the 1100m here may do the trip as he remains right down in the weights. Looks open to improvement second-up and can get the job done. SCREAM (1) brings some solid form across from Victoria in his first run for the new barn. He won well in similar grade two back at Hanging Rock and backed up that effort at Stony Creek. Webster's claim is a bonus and she can make a winning start to his career out west. I'M EUGENE (6) stuck on well over the 1200m journey here last time out and comes back in trip today. He's drawn well to be prominent once again and he has to be included  on that run. PRECAST (4) wasn't far away last time out and can put her best foot forward. ROYAL DEFENSE (9) can bounce back dropping in class.",
